Shadow of a Doubt.

The secret dossier on the Dreyfus affair.

In October 1894 a state scandal divided France against the backdrop of a tense international context. Captain Alfred Dreyfus was stripped of his rank and deported for having sent secret documents to the Germans. But doubt was soon cast on the accusers' integrity.
